  "text": "Storage 32 or 64GB + microSD up to 1TB CPU Hexa-core 2GHz Memory 3GB Operating System Fire OS 8 based on Android 11 Battery Rated for 13 hours of mixed use, supports wireless charging This is one of those Android tablets that's a good option if you're looking for something extremely affordable. While it does run Android, you will need to get your apps from Amazon's App Store. Of course, it becomes a tempting option at just $55. Let's be clear, the Amazon Fire HD 8 Plus is a budget Android tablet that only becomes appealing once it hits a certain price point. Now, with its original $120 price tag, it's a questionable purchase, but at its current discounted price of $55, it's an absolute no-brainer if you're looking for something cheap that gets the job done. This is probably the best price we're going to see on this tablet ahead of Prime Day 2025. Related Amazon Fire HD 8 Plus (2022) review: Who is this for? Kids? Adults? The compact size is tempting, but the grass is greener elsewhere. What's great about the Amazon Fire HD 8 Plus tablet? Amazon doesn't make a lot clear here when it comes to the specifications, mainly because there's nothing to write home about. Luckily, this model can handle the basics quite well, making it perfect for browsing the web, playing simple games, or watching movies. The Fire HD 8 Plus features an 8-inch screen, a hexa-core processor, 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage. The tablet also has a microSD card slot, allowing for storage expansion of up to 1TB. The battery life is also quite good, lasting up to 13 hours on a single charge. The tablet also has front and rear cameras, just in case you want to take some photos or videos, or get in some video calls. As mentioned before, it does run on Android, but you'll be getting your apps from Amazon’s Appstore. And while there are plenty of popular apps and games available, it's quite a bit less than what you'd find on Google's Play Store. That's something to be aware of just in case you need a specific app. Check the Amazon Appstore to make sure that what you need is available. If not, you might want to go with another option. Overall, this is a very simple tablet that gets the job done without costing a whole lot. Grab it now for just $55 during this sale, or if you want to wait it out, you can try your luck on Prime Day.",
