               \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-amazon-fire-hd-8-plus-tablet\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Amazon Fire HD 8 Plus tablet?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\u003cp\u003eAmazon doesn\u0026#39;t make a lot clear here when it comes to the specifications, mainly because there\u0026#39;s nothing to write home about. Luckily, this model can handle the basics quite well, making it perfect for browsing the web, playing simple games, or watching movies.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe Fire HD 8 Plus features an 8-inch screen, a hexa-core processor, 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage. The tablet also has a microSD card slot, allowing for storage expansion of up to 1TB. The battery life is also quite good, lasting up to 13 hours on a single charge.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe tablet also has front and rear cameras, just in case you want to take some photos or videos, or get in some video calls. As mentioned before, it does run on Android, but you\u0026#39;ll be getting your apps from Amazon’s Appstore. And while there are plenty of popular apps and games available, it\u0026#39;s quite a bit less than what you\u0026#39;d find on Google\u0026#39;s Play Store.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThat\u0026#39;s something to be aware of just in case you need a specific app. Check the Amazon Appstore to make sure that what you need is available. If not, you might want to go with another option. Overall, this is a very simple tablet that gets the job done without costing a whole lot. Grab it now for just $55 during this sale, or if you want to wait it out, you can try your luck on Prime Day.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
